blog.name: charambti
blog.title: Chara MBTI
blog.description: A group of people who type fictional characters. Search below.

title: BNHA Enneagram QuickType
body:
Izuku Midoriya: 9w1, Tritype 952 sp/so - Izuku is a natural problem-solver, always putting others’ happiness before his own. He relates to and admires Type 1 qualities, but behaves more like a type 9 in everyday life; Reserved, gentle and deeply concerned with others’ safety and wellbeing.

Yagi Toshinori: 2w1, Tritype 215 so/sp - Yagi is righteous, efficient and idealistic - in a concrete sense. He strives to help as many as possible, but is keenly aware of the reality of what he can actually do at any given moment. He’s empathetic and giving, being naturally in tune with other peoples’ needs, striving to become a symbol of peace and the best possible mentor to his students. All Might, as a persona, comes off more as a 2w3.

Ochako Uraraka: 9w1, Tritype 972 so/sp - Ochako is optimistic, high energy, caring and kind. Her motivations highly matches Izuku’s: she seeks harmony and balance in her personal life and believes in goodness. On another hand, her energy is very different to Izuku’s thanks to their Tritypes. Ochako is far more optimistic and social, while Izuku tends to be withdrawn and analytical.

Bakugo Katsuki: 8w7, Tritype 835 sx/so - Bakugo is incredibly blunt, to the point of being cruel. He’s ambitious, an achiever and a “doer”: ready to take on the next challenge as soon as possible. I’ve seen him frequently typed as an 837, but his thinking actually tends to be careful and analytical in battle. His impulsiveness might come from being an unhealthy 8 with a 7 wing.

Shouto Todoroki: 4w5, Tritype 458 sp/sx  - Todoroki is an introvert and an individualist. His main motive is asserting his own identity apart from his father’s influence, and although he seems confronting and cold at first, he opens up to those who are able to see him for who he truly is.

Tenya Iida: 1w2, Tritype 162 sp/so  - Iida is dutiful and constantly concerned with efficiency. Although he’s the orderly, critical archetype, Iida also greatly values loyalty and friendship. Upholding rules and traditions comes along with the desire to be helpful and constructive.

Momo Yaoyorozu: 5w6, Tritype 539 sp/so - Momo is smart, efficient and friendly, she’s both goal-oriented and cooperative, finding it easy to work with others to achieve a common goal. A great strategist, her intelligence shines through when she’s her most confident, although she can be insecure and overly concerned with other’s perception of her thanks to her wing and Tritype

Denki Kaminari: 7w6, Tritype 739 so/sx - Laidback, extroverted and an entertainer, Denki enjoys being the center of attention and being perceived positively by his peers. He’s friendly, charismatic and a bit scattered-brained, but is capable of great growth when he’s able to focus.

Eijiro Kirishima: 2w1, Tritype 279 so/sx - Kirishima is very difficult to type, because he has the attitudes and energy of a Type 7, but his backstory seems to suggest both his basic desires and fears are far more related to being accepted, loved and useful to those around him. He emanates a friendly, accepting aura, is brave, dutiful and has a strong sense of right and wrong, but is able to put those preconceptions aside to help others.

Summary:

After a night of passion after a baseball game Ochaco and Bakugo find themselves dealing with something neither of them ever wanted to deal with. Now facing the life of unexpected teen parents, they have to rely on not only themselves but the friends and family they have to get through what seems like a daunting task. Tears, laughter, the ups and downs of this relationship as it goes forward.

A KacChako fanfic. Hasn’t been beta read as of yet.
